 @AmanSharma-tt9ii  bro i have taken both policies in last 10 days so i cant tell about the service..but i have checked from gov site disclosure that both companies have good icr and claim settlement ratio...they both have icr between 60 to 70 which is grt..

Optima gave me 5 lkh cover for 8300 rs which has features like 50% no claim bonus every year so after 2 yrs my cover will be 10 lkh for same premium(upto 100%)..Nd restored amount after a claim  can be used for same illness again in the same year..Its has daily cash feature added which makes premium high , which is valid if u used shared accomodation,so that is of no use.

Icici gave the same cover for 5600 with critcal illnes cover of 9 illness..i didnt took opd nd hospital cash benefit bcoz the opd is only covered for 5k nd hospital cash is for 10 days only , so it is of no usee..if u however choose all three options dn it will cost u 9.5k which is high..so better choose critical illness only nd take high sum insured like 10 lkh for less than 8k..it has 10% no claim bonus upto 50% of sum insured but it has a waiting period of 2 yrs for any pre existing disease(optima has 3 yrs waiting),no claim bonus is not a big deal if u r fit ..hopefully u will not need that in coming years bcoz 5 or 7 lkh is enough for an individual even without ncb..so pay low nd take lombard nd take topup if u want..family flaoter will cost u even less..the restoration feature is same ..but it cant be used for same illness again in the same year..

